I used 1 T butter and 1 T flour, cooked it until light brown. Meantime I cut up a 28 oz can of whole tomatoes, added a scant 1/4 t of baking soda and 1 T of sugar. When roux was light brown I added 1/2 cup whole milk and 1/2 cup skim to roux. Stirred with a whisk and cooked until slightly thickened. Added 1 chicken bouillon cube and then the tomatoes. Warmed the soup, added a little more sugar to taste, then blended it. Tastes like Campbell's only better and healthier. That was exactly what I was going for.

