YUM ... this is the first time I've made tomato soup, and this was an easy, quick and delicious recipe. After reading other reviews, I adjusted the recipe a little. I used one 28 oz. can crushed tomatoes w/puree and one 28 oz. can fire roasted tomatoes. I added a little minced celery when I softened the onion. Because I used extra tomatoes ... I had to adjust the sugar to a tablespoon and I adjusted the salt to 2 tsp. And instead of 4 cups of milk ... to make it a little healthier ... I used 2 cups 1% milk and 1 cup chicken broth. After it simmered I puree the soup in a food processor (I don't own an immersion blender) instead of straining. Delicious, healthy and oh so easy!!

