Easy, simple, and delicious. Be sure to cook the flour in the butter for at least two foamy minutes otherwise your resulting soup may taste a bit floury. Don't forget the baking soda, it's one of the secrets to making the soup turn out right.

Rating: 4
My mother told me the way to make cream of tomato soup was to make the white sauce (roux) and tomatoes sauce separate and mix when hot to prevent curdling. The addition of baking soda to the hot tomatoes mixture results in the smoothest soup. If you are using fresh tomatoes, cooking first is important to soften the skin and seeds. I have always adjusted the tomatoes to white sauce mixture depending on what I have. I have used fresh tomatoes, canned tomatoes or a jar of spaghetti sauce. The best was when I used hot pepper infused olive oil to sauté some onions, celery and peppers first and then added the tomatoes. Always use a stick blender on the tomatoes prior to combining with white sauce. I have blended broccoli into this soup with wonderful results. Carrots work too. My kids like this soup over noodles. For company, I like to serve it over lump crab.

