Rating: 4
I give this 4 forks with the following provisions: In order to make this soup come out right, and I have made this numerous times now, is to do the following.... Use three 14.5 oz cans of tomatoes (or fresh equivalent) and up to 8 oz of tomato paste. Cook the onion, add the flour, add the milk, etc as specified. Then add the tomatoes, simmer for a minute. Then use a stick blender or blend it in a blender. Then, add tomato paste to taste and blend it in to the soup. Blending is a must. Do not strain or it will be very bland. If you follow this, you should find it very good....certainly much better than Cambell's.

